ce:section.ce:para:
Considering the multimodal synergistic in overcoming tumor MDR and eradicating tumors, thereinto, versatile nanoparticles (USC NPs) with synergistic therapeutic effects were facilely prepared (Fig. 1
                     ) via assembling chemotherapeutic drugs UA and SF (
                        Fig. S1
                     ), after assembled with CDs PSs through hydrogen bond, the corresponding products synthesized via such a facile and green assembly can be endowed with remarkable features. First of all, the particle size of USC NPs was significantly increased compared to CDs, which is more beneficial for their accumulation at tumor sites due to the EPR effects; Moreover, the design was expected to accomplish synergistic therapeutic efficiency, after one treatment cycle, the combination of chemotherapy (US NPs) and phototherapy (CDs) were expected to achieve effective tumor eradication without recurrence; Most importantly, the CDs PSs with high ROS generation performance and nucleolus targeting capacity, which provided a more effective and ideal site for cancer therapy. All in all, our NPs can give an entire extension to the effect of “killing three birds with one stone”. This strategy can overcome the impediments of mono-chemotherapy, for instance, the dissatisfaction of traditional chemotherapy against cancer includes nonspecific drug accumulation, low bioavailability, difficulty to overcome the heterogeneity and MDR of cancers, which cause severe systemic side effects and reoccurrence of tumors. In turn, such a strategy elevated cancer therapeutic efficacies and diminished undesired side effects.
